      "content": "The concept of using geometry to subtly steer temperament is largely in the realm of speculative design theory, rather than established scientific consensus. Familiarity certainly lowers cognitive guardrails, making us more accepting of stimuli without conscious analysis. Some researchers study how mathematical ratios in art affect human comfort, but the idea that a specific repeating plaid can hijack temperament is not widely substantiated. Ultimately, the influence is usually subtle priming rather than direct command.",
